args: No, and I've looked everywhere.\nWhere could she have gone...?
Sounds like she was pretty shaken when\nshe heard ya didn't remember how you\ntwo met.
Maybe there's some kinda clue in that?
She mentioned me helping her look for\nher parents, but there's no way I'd forget\nsomething like that.
I had a look around Chelsea's room to see\nif there might be any clues.
Nothing that seemed like it might speak\nto her whereabouts. I did find these two\ndolls most curious, however.
They look like sylvans...\nA man and a woman.
Mind fillin' us in there, pal?
Right. Back before I ever came to the\nHalidom, I was doing an errand for\nmy village...
Hey, you. Whatcha doin' out here?
I... I'm looking for my dolls. They're of\nmy Mama and Papa. I love them...
It's gonna be hard in the dark.\nLet me help you.
'Course. You look around here, and I'll\nstart searching over there.
THAT'S where we first met. And if I know\nChelsea, that's probably where she's\nheaded right now!
Sounds like ya better get movin'.
(This is where we met, before fate brought\nus together again on that mountain.)
(I was so sure Luccy shared my feelings...)
L-Luccy?! You're here!\nDoes that mean you...?
Yep, I remember. We found the dolls\nof your mom and dad right here.
Sorry for letting it skip my mind all\nthis time.
I'm just happy you remember. Tee hee!
Still, I don't think it's fair to call our\nmeeting ＂fate.＂ I just did what anyone\nwoulda done.
No. What you said to me that day saved\nmy life.
Oh? I don't really remember saying\nanything that profound...
There's still so much you don't know...
Luccy. Can I tell you a story about my\npast? About my family.

When I was little, my parents and I left the
woodland village we lived in and moved
to a human town so they could work
as apothecaries.
＂We can better the world by spreading\nsylvan knowledge.＂ They always used\nto say that.

I thought they were the coolest, chasing
their dream so intently. I wanted to help
however I could, so I worked in their
store a lot.

But the humans were not as supportive.
They refused to accept us, and burned
the shop to the ground. And my parents,
they... They both...
I was taken in by some relatives in my\nold village, but since I'd already left once,\nI was branded a traitor to sylvan kind.
I was shunned, and people whispered\nbehind my back. Eventually, I decided\nto leave again, this time for good.
What point was there in staying? They\ncouldn't understand my parents' dream,\nand they couldn't understand me, either.
But then I met you, and my world suddenly\nbecame brighter.
All thanks to what you said to me when\nyou found Mama and Papa.
Whoa, so you modeled these dolls on your\nfolks, huh? You guys must be really close.
Yes... I want to be just like them.
They tried to use sylvan knowledge to\nbetter the world, but nobody understood\ntheir dream.
Sounds like your folks and I would\nget along.
I feel the same way about spreading\nsylvan knowledge—and my village\nwas also pretty down on the idea.
I think everyone could benefit from sharing\ntheir discoveries with each other.
That way, we all grow together. So I think\nwhat your parents were trying to do was\nreally cool!
Hearing that brought me back from\nthe brink.
I realized I wasn't alone. And that made\nme so, so happy.
You're not going to take it back now,\nare you?
You're the only one who understands my\nfeelings, Luccy.
So our meeting MUST have been fate.
If we don't get married, I...
Chelsea. Close your eyes for a second.
Huh? Why? Wait... A-are we gonna kiss?!
This is so sudden... But okay!\nTee hee!
Did that snap you out of it?
This has gone way too far already.\nYou need to open your eyes and see\nwhat's really going on around you.

You were hurt. Nobody around you
understood you or your parents,
so you felt alone. And I'm sure that
was really hard.
But the world is full of people who DO\nunderstand. You just stopped looking.
I might've been the first one you met,\nbut the Halidom is full of people who\nwill understand your feelings.
The humans in town didn't accept us.\nThe people in my village shunned me!\nNOBODY understands but YOU!
That's just not true, Chelsea. But if you\nneed me to prove that to you, then I will.
Come on, let's head back to the castle.
